==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Discomposure
<hw>Dis`com*po"sure</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state of being discomposed; disturbance; disorder; agitation;
perturbation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No <qex>discomposure</qex> stirred her features.</q>
<rj><qau>Akenside.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Discordance; disagreement of parts.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discompt</ent>⟦br⟧
